article.headline: Rochester (Mich.) 59, E. Illinois 56
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Stavros Schizas and Dramell Hogan scored 17 points each and Rochester (Mich.) defeated Eastern Illinois 59-56 on Wednesday afternoon. Rochester is an NAIA school. Schizas was 3 of 4 from 3-point range and had four rebounds. Hogan was 6 of 12 from the field and grabbed five rebounds. Drew Maynard posted a double-double, with 15 points and 11 rebounds. Rochester led 29-25 at halftime. Rochester shot 44 percent from the field for the game, while the Panthers shot just 37 percent. Sherman Blanford had 11 points and nine rebounds for the Panthers (2-4). Morris Woods also had 11 points. Josh Piper added 10.
